records.addlTxt: Signed and filed: Marsy's Law Protective Order

Defendant Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Arial Jade Rosenberg in court for Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson.  Attorney Brittany Skye Kachingwe in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a status conference.  State filed Marsy's Law for Protective Order.  Arguments heard.  Court grants State's motion for protective order. Order for Protective Order signed and filed by the Court.  Court informs parties and Defendant that the no contact order will go into effect if bond is posted.  Defense acknowledges receipt of discovery but requests additional time to review discovery with client.  Court scheduled a status conference.  Case adjourned to Branch 11, Rm 608 CH.
Status conference scheduled for November 15, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson not in court, in custody.  Attorney Jason Findling in court on behalf of Arial Jade Rosenberg for Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson.  Attorney Dennis Murphy in court on behalf of Brittany Skye Kachingwe for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a status conference. Defense counsel is in trial and requests a status date. Court advised the state that the orders filed will be addressed at the next court date. Case remains calendared in Branch 11.
Status conference scheduled for October 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Filed: Marsy's Law Motion for Protective Order.

Defendant Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson in court with attorney Arial Jade Rosenberg.  Defendant Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson appeared by video means with Attorney.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 11, Judge Swanson. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 11.  Scheduling conference scheduled for September 29, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire & Waiver
State Public Defender - Order Appointing Counsel.  Received and Filed.  nk

Court ordered no contact with C.S.E, M.L.T, K.M.T, C.N, K.L.U, M.S, B.J.C, C.D.R, E.V, R.H.K, and R.C.K.
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5. If an Electronic Monitoring Device (GPS) is unavailable and Cash Bail has been paid, Defendant to be released and placed on the Electronic Monitoring (GPS) waiting list. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson in court with attorney Meera L Al-Henaey.  Defendant Dekyrus Ahmud Jamal Peterson in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
 Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Swanson, Branch 11.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.
